{
  "texts": [
    "Usually, even major distortions of saliency maps did not reduce human performance.",
    "If anything, a higher quality of saliency maps led to overreliance on the AI (Maehigashi et al., 2023a).",
    "This is not to say that it is unimportant or even undesirable to highlight areas that are actually relevant.",
    "Rather, it reiterates the importance of matching the cognitive task requirements of user studies to the information capabilities of saliency maps.",
    "If saliency maps are irrelevant to the cognitive processes needed for solving the task, their quality will not matter, either."
  ]
}